		<div id="siteNotice"><script type='text/javascript'>if (wgNotice != '') document.writeln(wgNotice);</script></div>		<h1 id="firstHeading" class="firstHeading">Earth Day</h1>
		<div id="bodyContent">
			<h3 id="siteSub">From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia</h3>
			<div id="contentSub"></div>
									<div id="jump-to-nav">Jump to: <a href="#column-one">navigation</a>, <a href="#searchInput">search</a></div>			<!-- start content -->
			<div class="thumb tright">
<div class="thumbinner" style="width:322px;"><a href="/wiki/File:Earth_flag_PD.jpg" class="image" title="Unofficial Earth Day flag, by John McConnell: the Blue Marble on a blue background."><img alt="" src="http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Earth_flag_PD.jpg/320px-Earth_flag_PD.jpg" width="320" height="214" border="0" class="thumbimage" /></a>
<div class="thumbcaption">
<div class="magnify"><a href="/wiki/File:Earth_flag_PD.jpg" class="internal" title="Enlarge"><img src="/skins-1.5/common/images/magnify-clip.png" width="15" height="11" alt="" /></a></div>
Unofficial Earth Day flag, by John McConnell: the <a href="/wiki/Blue_Marble" title="Blue Marble" class="mw-redirect">Blue Marble</a> on a blue background.</div>
</div>
</div>
<p><b>Earth Day</b> is one of two <a href="/wiki/Observance" title="Observance" class="mw-redirect">observances</a>, both held annually during spring in the <a href="/wiki/Northern_hemisphere" title="Northern hemisphere" class="mw-redirect">northern hemisphere</a>, and autumn in the <a href="/wiki/Southern_hemisphere" title="Southern hemisphere" class="mw-redirect">southern hemisphere</a>. These are intended to inspire awareness of and appreciation for the <a href="/wiki/Earth" title="Earth">Earth</a>'s environment. The <a href="/wiki/United_Nations" title="United Nations">United Nations</a> celebrates an Earth Day each year on the <a href="/wiki/Equinox" title="Equinox">March equinox</a>, a tradition which was founded by peace activist <a href="/wiki/John_McConnell_(peace_activist)" title="John McConnell (peace activist)">John McConnell</a> in 1969.</p>
<p>A second Earth Day, which was founded by U.S. Senator <a href="/wiki/Gaylord_Nelson" title="Gaylord Nelson">Gaylord Nelson</a> as an environmental <a href="/wiki/Teach-in" title="Teach-in">teach-in</a> in 1970, is celebrated in many countries each year on <span class="mw-formatted-date" title="04-22"><a href="/wiki/April_22" title="April 22">April 22</a></span>.</p>
